      "side": 1,
      "message": "In your commit message you state that using `object_path::str` is an anti-pattern and that `string()` should be used instead (as also mentioned in the comment you\u0027ve added to `std::string str`.) But at the same time, the comment added directly on `string()` itself then says:\n\u003e avoid using this function for new code if \u0027filename()\u0027 / \u0027parent_path()\u0027 / ... will do.\n\nThis is, in my opinion, confusing as they point in opposite directions. One says \"prefer `string()`\", the other says \"avoid `string()`\". It\u0027d help to clarify the intended hierarchy of preference here.",
      "revId": "4b5f21cc81742c37dcffeb1b59a7277c9c4e9180",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
