      "writtenOn": "2026-06-12T13:38:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The comments are indirection among each other.\n\nThe API user (instead of being left guessing) is directed to the preferred API.\n\nThe order of preference is (from most to least preferred):\n- `object_path::filename()` | `object_path::parent_path()` | ...\n- `object_path::string()`\n- direct `object_path::str` reading the internal value\n- direct `object_path::str` access, changing the internal value in some way\n\nThe problem is that it really depends on the use-case and the amount of refactoring someone is willing to do which one they will use.\n\nThere is no single direct replacement for `object_path::string()` i could point to, right?\n\nI\u0027m very much open to change the comments if you would like to suggest a change (gerrit has a feature to directly suggest an edit)",
      "parentUuid": "948fb31f_fc4f9f0c",
      "revId": "4b5f21cc81742c37dcffeb1b59a7277c9c4e9180",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
